Remarks
. 

Tyrphonothrus kimberleyi


sp. nov
.

differs from other members of the genus by the following combination of characters: 
1
) the long, thin interlamellar setae; 
2
) the straight, transverse anterior notogastral margin; 
3
) the foveolate notogaster; 
4
) the vestigial, posterior notogastral ridge in the form of semicircular indentations; 
5
) the extremely short setae 
p
1
; 
6
) the epimeral setal formula 
2
- 
1-3
- 
3
; 
7
) the seven pairs of genital setae; 
8
) the two pairs of anal setae; 
9
) the sclerotised transverse region on the anterior margin of the adanal plate.
